# Frontend Standards (React + Telegram UI)

## Stack and Components
- Build UI using React patterns already used in the project.
- Actively use `@telegram-apps/telegram-ui` components as the default UI layer.
- Prefer extending/composing ui-kit components over creating custom primitives from scratch.
- Keep presentation components focused on one UI responsibility.

## State and UX
- Keep state minimal, explicit, and local by default.
- Handle loading, empty, and error states for user-facing screens.
- Avoid hidden side effects inside render logic and component lifecycle flows.

## Quality
- Reuse existing project patterns for folder structure, naming, and component APIs.
- Add or update frontend tests for meaningful behavior changes where coverage exists.

## Delivery Artifacts (Mandatory)
- Follow `.cursor/rules/feature-delivery-workflow.mdc` for every frontend feature task.
- Keep `.cursor/active/{feature-slug}/plan.md`, `progress.md`, and `result.md` updated.
- Publish final outcome in `docs/features/{feature-slug}.md`.
- Append every meaningful frontend action to `.cursor/memory/logs/action-log.md` with changed file links.
